==English==

===Verb===
'''[[see]] [[the]] [[forest]] [[for]] [[the]] [[tree]]s'''
# {{idiom}} To discern an overall pattern from a mass of detail; to see the bigger picture, or the broader, more general situation.  Generally used in the negative.
#: ''Smith is good at detail, but can't '''see the forest for the trees'''.''

===Alternative spellings===
*[[see the forest through the trees]]
* [[can't see the wood for the trees ]]
